              PIC
              ) was equally large in fully and partially bistable cells, but there were substantial differences in how I
              PIC
              was activated and deactivated. In fully bistable cells, the offset of I
              PIC
              on the descending phase of the triangular voltage command occurred at a substantially more hyperpolarized voltage then its onset on the rising phase. Thus the I-V function of fully bistable cells exhibited marked hysteresis. Partially bistable cells had significantly less hysteresis. The lack of hysteresis in partially bistable cells was due to a greater decay of I
              PIC
