              PIC
              in fully bistable cells corresponded to a similarly large hysteresis for the thresholds of their F-I functions. The reduced onset-offset difference for I
              PIC
              in partially bistable cells corresponded to a lack of hysteresis in F-I thresholds. Thus the properties of I
              PIC
              accounted for the main differences in the F-I behavior seen between fully and partially bistable cells.},
